There are, however, conditions and limits to the definitions of Attributes, though they are not the same as those of Substances. Every Substance to be definable must be a Species. Every Attribute must be a Property, i. e. must be capable of demonstration by its cause. Accidents then, as merely contingent attributes, are incapable os definition. This limitationâ€š however, is merely relative to the degree of our knowledge of the matter. The advance of Science may transform Acci- dents into Properties, and thus furnish the requisite means of definition.
